      <Value><![CDATA[[
  {
    "key": "5b75b215-e5c2-4426-91e6-8547934af454",
    "name": "About QMU",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "About QMU",
    "content": "<p><img src=\"?mode=crop&amp;width=800\" alt=\"A panoramic view of QMU campus\" width=\"800\" height=\"266.6666666666667\" data-udi=\"umb://media/d9348bd929454fbca712d38d5401f705\"></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"lead-big\">About QMU</span></p>\n<p>We aim to shape a better world through education, research and innovation. In doing so, we enable individuals and communities to flourish. <br><br>Our person-centred approach to learning makes us stand out from other universities, along with our focus on making society better. Our academic offering also distinguishes us. We dedicate ourselves to subjects where we can provide a distinctive offering - in healthcare; social sciences; creative arts; business; management and enterprise; and primary and secondary teaching.<br><br>Outward looking, we have a strong ethos of partnership and collaboration. At our modern campus, we benefit from easy access to the centre of Edinburgh, Scotland's vibrant and historic capital city.</p>\n<p>We are pioneers in inclusiveness and we embrace people from all backgrounds.<br><br>Find out more about the <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/a67713586dab42108759e724aece703d}\" title=\"History\">history of university</a>, along with information about <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/c193260b558648f29c85d69c8c088b80}\" title=\"Quality\">our governance</a>, the <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/1bf80f3b042746249bae3810ecc8ca7d}\" title=\"Chancellor, Vice-Chancellor and Senior Leadership Team\">Principal and Vice-Chancellor,</a> <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/1bf80f3b042746249bae3810ecc8ca7d}\" title=\"Chancellor, Vice-Chancellor and Senior Leadership Team\">the senior leadership team</a> and <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/23ed7ab2bf2b4808b948dca16bea8636}\" title=\"Partnerships\">our collaborative partners</a>.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"lead-big\">About the Psychology, Sociology and Education Division</span></p>\n<p>Located within the School of Arts, Social Sciences and Management, the <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/6e5272fa3f544060af877ca7f121f21c}\" title=\"Psychology, Sociology and Education\">Division of Psychology, Sociology and Education</a> presently hosts a number of undergraduate and postgraduate programmes in Teacher Education.</p>\n<p>Psychology, Sociology and Education deliver some modules shared across programmes, thus enabling cross-disciplinary collaboration and the provision of robust social science degrees. Postgraduate programmes within the division include a Masters in Research (MRes) and a Postgraduate Diploma in Secondary Education in Home Economics (PGDE).</p>\n<p>Division members are research active and submit to two units of assessment in the REF, with a third (Education) being planned for the next cycle. We also support and benefit from a number of Visiting Lecturers, PhD students and Research Assistants across the three disciplines. This role would be to join this growing division and become a full and active member of the vibrant and committed team.</p>\n<p>The Division hosts the <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/9e59330129ac41028d861633fdcb6a2d}\" title=\"Centre for Applied Social Sciences\">Centre for Applied Social Sciences (CASS)</a> which conducts research into social issues that affect people’s lives locally, nationally, and internationally. Its applied approach produces research that has a theoretical and practical focus and that brings together interdisciplinary expertise in addressing issues of individual and social relevance.</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "238bf616-9af7-491e-aa4a-e3e77efdccad",
    "name": "Qualified Teacher Roles",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Qualified Teacher Roles",
    "content": "<p><img src=\"?width=787&amp;height=263&amp;mode=max\" alt=\"Teacher reading with a group of school children\" width=\"787\" height=\"263\" data-udi=\"umb://media/5dc34b003e97461a8eb2eca309b23868\"></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"lead-big\">The Roles - Teaching Qualification Required</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>3</strong> x <strong>Full Time Positions</strong> – <strong>(Teaching Qualification required):</strong> <br><strong>Assistant Lecturer in Teacher Education</strong> or <strong>Lecturer in Teacher Education</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>and</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>1</strong> x <strong>Senior Lecturer in Teacher Education</strong><span class=\"lead\"><br></span><span class=\"lead\"></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span class=\"lead\"><strong>School: </strong></span>Arts, Social Sciences and Management<br><span class=\"lead\"><strong>Division: </strong></span><a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/6e5272fa3f544060af877ca7f121f21c}\" title=\"Psychology, Sociology and Education\">Psychology, Sociology and Education</a><br><span class=\"lead\"><strong>Responsible to: </strong></span>Associate Head of Division<br><span class=\"lead\"><strong>Location: </strong></span>Edinburgh (<a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/a713799de0204325bb063efbd482f213}\" title=\"Location and Getting Here\">Musselburgh Campus</a>)<span class=\"lead\"><br></span><span class=\"lead\"></span></p>\n<p>-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p><span class=\"lead\">Assistant Lecturer in Teacher Education</span></p>\n<p><strong>Contract Basis:</strong> Permanent, open ended<br><strong>Contract Type:</strong> Teaching and Scholarship<br><strong>Hours:</strong> Full Time, 35 hours per week (1.0 FTE) or Part Time, 17.5 hours per week (0.5 FTE)<br><strong>Salary/Grade:</strong> Grade 7 £34,304- £38,587 (with possible progression to £43,434)<br><strong>Closing Date:</strong> Sunday 19th June 2022<br><strong>REF:</strong> CVSY059A</p>\n<p><a href=\"/{localLink:umb://media/d2517d964f2041138e9b0fdb332eb893}\" title=\"Job Description Assistant Lecturer In Teacher Education (Teaching And Scholarship) May 2022\"><span class=\"blue-btn\">Asst. Lecturer in Teacher Education - Job Description and Person Specification (Word Format)</span></a></p>\n<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br></p>\n<p><span class=\"lead\">Lecturer in Teacher Education</span></p>\n<p><strong>Contract Basis:</strong> Permanent, open ended<br><strong>Contract Type:</strong> Teaching and Scholarship<br><strong>Hours:</strong> Full Time, 35 hours per week (1.0 FTE) or Part Time, 17.5 hours per week (0.5 FTE)<br><strong>Salary/Grade:</strong> Grade 8 £39,739 - £50,296 (with possible progression to £56,587)<br><strong>Closing Date:</strong> Sunday 19th June 2022<br><strong>REF:</strong> CVSY059A</p>\n<p><a href=\"/{localLink:umb://media/fc24b9f2d343420a9b74e251e19829ea}\" title=\"Job Description Lecturer In Teacher Education (Teaching And Scholarship) May 2022\"><span class=\"blue-btn\">Lecturer in Teacher Education - Job Description and Person Specification (Word Format) </span></a><a href=\"/{localLink:umb://media/d2517d964f2041138e9b0fdb332eb893}\" title=\"Job Description Assistant Lecturer In Teacher Education (Teaching And Scholarship) May 2022\"></a></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p><span class=\"lead\">Senior Lecturer in Teacher Education</span><br><strong>Contract Basis:</strong> Permanent, open ended<br><strong>Contract Type:</strong> Teaching and Scholarship<br><strong>Hours:</strong> Full Time<br><strong>Salary/Grade:</strong> Grade 9 £51,799 - £60,022 (with possible progression to £71,637)<br><strong>Closing Date:</strong> Sunday 19th June 2022<br><strong>REF:</strong> CVSY059A<br><br><a href=\"/{localLink:umb://media/76bfdc75a9384b1c95e7bd8890c0c00f}\" title=\"Job Description Senior Lecturer In Teacher Education (Teaching And Scholarship) May 2022\"><span class=\"blue-btn\">Senior Lecturer in Teacher Education - Job Description and Person Specification (Word Format)</span></a></p>\n<p> </p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "2f34f149-38a3-44ef-acc7-e4319e2fa306",
    "name": "Education Roles",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "Education Roles",
    "content": "<p><img src=\"?width=638&amp;height=213&amp;mode=max\" alt=\"Photo of 3 children listening to teacher\" width=\"638\" height=\"213\" data-udi=\"umb://media/c29dc85881ff49b089aacedca14f967a\"></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>In 2018 Queen Margaret University was selected by the Scottish Government to offer a new suite of Teacher Education programmes and we welcomed our first cohorts in September 2019. We are excited to be recruiting for our growing Teacher Education team and are seeking to appoint three Lecturers or Assistant Lecturers to be part of our growing provision. The successful postholder(s) will teach on our GTCS accredited degrees in Teacher Education designed to contribute to the development of the next generation of primary and secondary school teachers as well as contribute to modules shared with Psychology and/or Sociology.</p>\n<p>This is an exciting opportunity for career development and progression given the growth in educational programmes and research in this area which the university is keen to expand further. The purpose of the role is to provide excellent and innovative teaching both online and on campus; provide academic guidance; guide curriculum and programme design and undertake research in the field of sociology of education or psychology of education or childhood studies. The post offers the opportunity to work with colleagues in the Division of Psychology, Sociology &amp; Education, as well as across the university, and to broaden our collaborative engagement with educational professionals across the sector.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"lead lead-big\">Education Roles</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>2.8FTE</strong> Positions\n<p><strong>Assistant Lecturer in Teacher Education</strong></p>\n<p>OR</p>\n<p><strong>Lecturer in Teacher Education</strong></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>School: </strong>Arts, Social Sciences and Management<br><strong>Division: </strong><a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/6e5272fa3f544060af877ca7f121f21c}\" title=\"Psychology, Sociology and Education\">Psychology, Sociology and Education</a><br><strong>Responsible to: </strong>Associate Head of Division<br><strong>Location: </strong>Edinburgh (<a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/a713799de0204325bb063efbd482f213}\" title=\"Location and Getting Here\">Musselburgh Campus</a>)</p>\n<p>-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\n<p><span class=\"lead\">Assistant Lecturer in Teacher Education<br>(Psychology of Education OR Sociology of Education OR Childhood Studies)*<br></span></p>\n<p><strong>Contract Basis:</strong> Permanent, open ended<br><strong>Contract Type:</strong> Teaching and Scholarship<br><strong>Hours:</strong> Full Time, 35 hours per week (1.0 FTE) or Part Time, 17.5 hours per week (0.5 FTE)<br><strong>Salary/Grade:</strong> Grade 7 £34,304- £38,587 (with possible progression to £43,434)<br><strong>*Please state which area is of interest on your application</strong><br><strong>Closing Date:</strong> Sunday 19th June 2022<br><strong>REF:</strong> CVSY049A</p>\n<p><a href=\"/{localLink:umb://media/95a2a92a478f4337b4883db68f24330a}\" title=\"Job Description Asst Lecturer Psych.Soc.Childhood Teacher Education May2022\"><span class=\"blue-btn\">Assistant Lecturer in Teacher Education - Job Description and Person Specification (Word Format)</span></a></p>\n<p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br></p>\n<p><span class=\"lead\">Lecturer in Teacher Education<br>(Psychology of Education OR Sociology of Education OR Childhood Studies)*<br></span></p>\n<p><strong>Contract Basis:</strong> Permanent, open ended<br><strong>Contract Type:</strong> Teaching and Scholarship<br><strong>Hours:</strong> Full Time, 35 hours per week (1.0 FTE) or Part Time, 17.5 hours per week (0.5 FTE)<br><strong>Salary/Grade:</strong> Grade 8 £39,739 - £50,296 (with possible progression to £56,587)<br>*<strong>Please state which area is of interest on your application</strong><br><strong>Closing Date:</strong> Sunday 19th June 2022<br><strong>REF:</strong> CVSY049A</p>\n<p><a href=\"/{localLink:umb://media/1f4c7518a0fb4acc900f079d04182ad9}\" title=\"Job Description Lecturer Psych.Soc.Childhood Teacher Education May 2022\"><span class=\"blue-btn\">Lecturer in Teacher Education - Job Description and Person Specification (Word Format)</span></a></p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "723994c2-bddd-490e-af27-f64c6c28bb02",
    "name": "What we Offer",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "What we Offer",
    "content": "<p><img src=\"?width=793&amp;height=265&amp;mode=max\" alt=\"QMU logo in blue against a white background\" width=\"793\" height=\"265\" data-udi=\"umb://media/1dfa730a810a41c5a80408cf1a8ae78c\"></p>\n<p><span class=\"lead-big\">What we Offer</span></p>\n<p>We are committed to equality of opportunity for all by providing a supportive and flexible and inclusive working environment, and we welcome applicants from diverse backgrounds. We are proud to hold an Athena SWAN Bronze Award which recognises the advancement of gender equality at QMU.</p>\n<p>We support a flexible approach to work as well additional benefits to help your work life balance such as a generous annual leave allowance, subsidised on-site gym membership, bike to work scheme and a range of discounts.</p>\n<p>We invest in your professional development, including through access to AdvanceHE Strategic Leadership programmes and HE sector mentoring through access to TRAMS.<br><br>We also offer:</p>\n<p>1. Wellbeing support with our 24 hour Employee Assistance Service, access to mental health support services and occupational health support</p>\n<p>2. Discounted <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/854bacf0350b4399af7c7ec40cbea646}\" title=\"QMU Sports Centre\">sports and leisure facilities</a> on campus</p>\n<p>3. Access to our <a href=\"/{localLink:umb://document/71b99825061d4a2e8bd48daeb9d7cfe2}\" title=\"Library\">learning resource centre</a></p>\n<p>4. Interest free travel loans</p>\n<p>5. Large variety of E-learning modules</p>"
  },
  {
    "key": "7a08ea07-4c6f-48be-aa5c-2d75bf4fa82d",
    "name": "How to Apply",
    "ncContentTypeAlias": "centralBlocks",
    "title": "How to Apply",
    "content": "<p><span class=\"lead-big\">How to Apply<br /><br /></span>Please visit our recruitment site using the links below to view the job description for all posts and to download the application form. <strong>*Please state clearly on your application which role you wish to be considered for*.</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://ce0011li.webitrent.com/ce0011li_webrecruitment/wrd/run/ETREC107GF.open?VACANCY_ID%3d54942953HD&amp;WVID=6368270VSq&amp;LANG=USA\" title=\"Apply for a Qualified Teacher Role at QMU\" data-anchor=\"?VACANCY_ID%3d54942953HD&amp;WVID=6368270VSq&amp;LANG=USA\"><span class=\"blue-btn\">Apply for a Qualified Teacher Role</span></a> <br />(i.e. Assistant Lecturer in Teacher Education | Lecturer in Teacher Education | Senior Lecturer in Teacher Education)<br /><br /><a href=\"https://ce0011li.webitrent.com/ce0011li_webrecruitment/wrd/run/ETREC107GF.open?VACANCY_ID%3d24677053HD&amp;WVID=6368270VSq&amp;LANG=USA\" title=\"Apply for other Teacher Education Role at QMU\" data-anchor=\"?VACANCY_ID%3d24677053HD&amp;WVID=6368270VSq&amp;LANG=USA\"><span class=\"blue-btn\">Apply for other Teacher Education Role</span></a> <br />(i.e. Assistant Lecturer in Teacher Education | Lecturer in Teacher Education)<br /><br />For any queries regarding the role or an informal chat please contact Dr Simon Hoult, Associate Head of Division of Psychology, Sociology and Education via email <a href=\"mailto:shoult@qmu.ac.uk\">shoult@qmu.ac.uk</a></p>\n<p>Should you have any queries regarding the application process or require any special assistance please contact Human Resources on email <a href=\"mailto:recruitment@qmu.ac.uk\" title=\"Email QMU Recruitment Team\"><span>recruitment@qmu.ac.uk</span></a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Closing Date for Applications is Sunday 19<sup>th</sup> June 2022.</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><em>Queen Margaret University is committed to equality of opportunity for all by providing a supportive, flexible and inclusive working environment, and we welcome applicants from diverse backgrounds. We are proud to hold an Athena SWAN Bronze Award which recognises the advancement of gender equality at QMU. Find out more about <a href=\"https://www.ecu.ac.uk/equality-charters/athena-swan/\" title=\"Athena Swan\">Athena SWAN </a></em><em>.  We have a number of family friendly policies and are happy to consider job share applications.</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>We are a Disability Confident Employer, should you require any specific arrangements during the recruitment process please note this on your application form or contact Human Resources on 0131 474 0000 or email </em></strong><a href=\"mailto:recruitment@qmu.ac.uk\" title=\"Email QMU Recruitment Team\"><em>recruitment@qmu.ac.uk</em></a></p>"
  }
]]]></Value>
